uk.ac.ebi.masscascade.alignment

Class Obiwarp

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ebi.masscascade.interfaces.CallableTask
      • uk.ac.ebi.masscascade.alignment.Obiwarp
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.concurrent.Callable<Container>, Task

    public class Obiwarp
extends CallableTask
    Class for profile aligning using Obiwarp. The class executes the Obiwarp binary with the given parameters and converts its output back into a list of aligned profiles. Input is provided in "lmata" format, which is generated on the fly from the profile container. The reference file, the converted reference profile container, is provided via the parameter map. The ObiwarpHelper class can be used to create the file and generate the mz bins.

    • Parameter REFERENCE_FILE - The lmata reference file.
    • Parameter PROFILE CONTAINER - The input profile container.
    • Parameter GAP_INIT - The gap penalty for initiating a gap.
    • Parameter GAP_EXTEND - The gap penaly for extending a gap.
    • Parameter RESPONSE - The responsiveness of warping [0 - 100].
    • Parameter EXECUTABLE - The path to the Obiwarp executable.
